value.value: A small RNA molecule that is the product of a longer exogenous or endogenous dsRNA, which is either a bimolecular duplex or very long hairpin, processed (via the Dicer pathway) such that numerous siRNAs accumulate from both strands of the dsRNA. siRNAs trigger the cleavage of their target molecules.
A primary transcript encoding a micro RNA.
Cytosolic SSU rRNA is an RNA component of the small subunit of cytosolic ribosomes.

definition.value: Renamed to cytosolic_SSU_rRNA from small_subunit_rRNA on 10 June 2021 as per restructuring of rRNA child terms. Updated definition to be consistent with format of other rRNA definitions. Request from EBI. See GitHub Issue #493.

value.value: Cytosolic LSU rRNA is an RNA component of the large subunit of cytosolic ribosomes.

definition.value: Renamed to cytosolic_LSU_rRNA from large_subunit_rRNA on 10 June 2021 as per restructuring of rRNA child terms. Updated definition to be consistent with format of other rRNA definitions. Request from EBI. See GitHub Issue #493.

value.value: Cytosolic 5S rRNA is an RNA component of the large subunit of cytosolic ribosomes in both prokaryotes and eukaryotes.

definition.value: Renamed from rRNA_5S to cytosolic_5S_rRNA on 27 May 2021 with the restructuring of rRNA child terms. Updated definition to be consistent with format of other rRNA definitions. Requested by EBI. See GitHub Issue #493.

value.value: Cytosolic 28S rRNA is an RNA component of the large subunit of cytosolic ribosomes in metazoan eukaryotes.

definition.value: Renamed from rRNA_28S to cytosolic_28S_rRNA on 27 May 2021 with the restructuring of rRNA child terms. Updated definition to be consistent with format of other rRNA definitions. Requested by EBI. See GitHub Issue #493.

value.value: A mitochondrial gene located in a maxicircle.
An RNA transcript that does not encode for a protein rather the RNA molecule is the gene product.

definition.value: A ncRNA is a processed_transcript, so it may not contain parts such as transcribed_spacer_regions that are removed in the act of processing. For the corresponding primary_transcripts, please see term SO:0000483 nc_primary_transcript.
A region that can be transcribed into a small temporal RNA (stRNA). Found in roundworm development.

value.value: A region of sequence containing one or more repeat units.
A repeat that is located at dispersed sites in the genome.

definition.value: A region that can be transcribed into a transfer-messenger RNA (tmRNA).

value.value: An intron which is spliced by the spliceosome.

definition.value: A region that can be transcribed into a transfer RNA (tRNA).

value.value: A region of a chromosome that has been introduced by backcrossing with a separate species.
A transcript that is monocistronic.
An intron (mitochondrial, chloroplast, nuclear or prokaryotic) that encodes a double strand sequence specific endonuclease allowing for mobility.
The sequence of one or more nucleotides added between two adjacent nucleotides in the sequence.
A match against an EST sequence.

definition.value: A feature where a segment of DNA has been rearranged from what it was in the parent cell.

value.value: A sequence within the micronuclear DNA of ciliates at which chromosome breakage and telomere addition occurs during nuclear differentiation.
A sequence eliminated from the genome of ciliates during nuclear differentiation.
A sequence that is conserved, although rearranged relative to the micronucleus, in the macronucleus of a ciliate genome.
An RNA synthesized on a DNA or RNA template by an RNA polymerase.

definition.value: Added relationship overlaps SO:0002300 unit_of_gene_expression with Mejia-Almonte et.al PMID:32665585 Aug 5, 2020.

value.value: The canonical 3' splice site has the sequence "AG".
The canonical 5' splice site has the sequence "GT".
A 3' splice site that does not have the sequence "AG".
A 5' splice site which does not have the sequence "GT".
A start codon that is not the usual AUG sequence.
A transcript that has been processed "incorrectly", for example by the failure of splicing of one or more exons.
Exonic splicing enhancers (ESEs) facilitate exon definition by assisting in the recruitment of splicing factors to the adjacent intron.
A region of nucleotide sequence targeted by a nuclease enzyme.

definition.value: DNA region representing open chromatin structure that is hypersensitive to digestion by DNase I.

value.value: A chromosomal translocation whereby the chromosomes carrying non-homologous centromeres may be recovered independently. These chromosomes are described as translocation elements. This occurs for some translocations, particularly but not exclusively, reciprocal translocations.
The space between two bases in a sequence which marks the position where a deletion has occurred.
A set of subregions selected from sequence contigs which when concatenated form a nonredundant linear sequence.
A match against cDNA sequence.
A gene that encodes a polycistronic transcript.
The initiator methionine that has been cleaved from a mature polypeptide sequence.
A gene that encodes a dicistronic transcript.
A gene that encodes an mRNA that is recoded.

SNPs are single base pair positions in genomic DNA at which different sequence alternatives exist in normal individuals in some population(s), wherein the least frequent variant has an abundance of 1% or greater.
A sequence used in experiment.
A short oligonucleotide sequence, of length on the order of 10's of bases; either single or double stranded.
A gene that encodes a transcript with stop codon readthrough.
A gene encoding an mRNA that has the stop codon redefined as pyrrolysine.
A sequence_feature with an extent of zero.

definition.value: A junction is a boundary between regions. A boundary has an extent of zero.

value.value: A comment about the sequence.
A region of sequence where the validity of the base calling is questionable.
A region of sequence where there may have been an error in the assembly.
